709109f-a.text:
To those of the Seventh who made the supreme sacrifice.
The 7th Regiment War Memorial at Fifth Avenue and 66th Street was unveiled today, the ninth anniversary of the battle of the Hindenburg line and accepted by Mayor Walker as the Regiment's gift to the City. It is dedicated to the 580 members of New Yorkts 7th Regiment, 107th Infantry,
who gave their lives in the World War.
8/29/1927  Wide World Photos

718414f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.
718414f-a.text:
Central Park: W.P.A. employees removing the 86th Street, crosstown car tracks that were laid on a transverse vehicular road through the Park. They ran in an easterly and westerly direction from West 86th Street and Central Park West to East 85th Street and Fifth Ave. This view is
slightly eastward of the first point.
September 29, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

718411f.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.
718411f.text:

and westward through the Park.
October 8, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

718412f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.
718412f-a.text:
Central Park: A view of W.P.A. employees removing the 86th Street car tracks in the western side of the Park on a transverse vehicular road that extends from West 86th Street and Central Park West to East 85th Street and Fifth Ave. This photo is taken slightly eastward of the first point.
September 29, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

718413f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.
718413f-a.text:

85th Streets.
September 29, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
